Name: VegaFairing
Title: Vega fairing
Description: A small fairing for small payloads.

Name: DecouplerVega
Title: Vega Payload Decoupler
Description: A stack decoupler for payloads releasing.

Name: Vega_Stage3
Title: Vega Dtage 3 (Zefiro 9)
Description: The Zefiro 9 is a copy of the second stage.

Name: Ariane6_Stage1
Title: P135 (three)
Description: The original proposal for Ariane 6 would have consisted of four P135 solid boosters and a cryogenic upper stage. Three P135 boosters strapped together would have made up the first stage, while a single P135 would serve as the second stage. This booster design was later dropped in favor of a cryogenic core with two or four P120 boosters.

Name: Ariane6_Stage2
Title: P135
Description: The P135 was intended to serve as the first and second stage of the Ariane 6 PPH. The first stage would have consisted of three P135 boosters, with a single booster acting as second stage.

Name: Diamant_Stage3
Title: Diamant stage 3
Description: A small solid fuel booster.

Name: Ariane4NoseCone2
Title: Ariane 4 solid booster's nosecone
Description: A small nosecone to put on the top of solid booster, to permit a better jettison.

Name: Ariane4RadialDecoupler
Title: Ariane 4 radial decoupler
Description: A radial decoupler to jettison SRB.

Name: Vega_Stage1
Title: Vega Stage 1 (P80)
Description: The P80 is a solid fuel booster based on the Ariane 5 EAP.

Name: Ariane4NoseCone
Title: Ariane 4 liquid booster's nosecone
Description: A small nosecone to put on the top of liquid booster, to permit a better jettison.

Name: Ariane5_FairingBig
Title: Ariane 5 big fairing
Description: A big fairing for big payload.

Name: Ariane4Stage1
Title: Ariane 4 L220 (1st stage)
Description: The first stage of Ariane 4 powered by 4 Vulcain V engines.

Name: Ariane4Stage3
Title: Ariane 4 H10 III (3rd stage)
Description: The cryogenic third stage of the variety used in the majority of Ariane 4 launches. Powered by a HM7B++ engine, and equiped with small attitude control thrusters fueled with gaseous hydrogen (boil-off from the main tank).

Name: Ariane6_Fairing
Title: Ariane 6 fairing
Description: A fairing to protect payload.

Name: Ariane4Stage2
Title: Ariane 3/4 L33 (2nd stage)
Description: Nearly nothing changed since Ariane 1.

Name: Ariane5_EAP
Title: EAP MPS-241A
Description: Ariane 5's solid booster

Name: DecouplerDiamant
Title: Diamant Payload Decoupler
Description: A small decoupler for small payloads releasing.

Name: DiamantFairing
Title: Diamant fairing
Description: A small fairing for a small satellite.

Name: Diamant_Stage2
Title: Diamant A/B 2nd stage "Topaze"
Description: The second stage of the Diamant rocket, and simultaneously the first stage of the Topaze sounding rocket. For complete realism add some small solid rockets at the top of this stage to spin stabilize the rocket before firing the third stage.

Name: Diamant_Stage1
Title: Diamant A 1st stage "Emeraude"
Description: First stage of the Diamant A rocket, powered by an LRBA Vexin engine.

Name: Ariane5_engine
Title: Ariane 5 engine Vulcain II
Description: The Vulcain II is the engine of the Ariane 5 cryogenic stage.

Name: DiamantAsterix
Title: A-1 "Asterix"
Description: The first French satellite in orbit.

Name: Ariane5_NoseCone
Title: Ariane 5 EAP nosecone
Description: A small nosecone to put on the top of EAPs, to permit a better jettison and land smoothly with a parachute.

Name: Ariane4Sylda
Title: Ariane 3/4 SYLDA
Description: A system to place 2 payloads in the Ariane 4 fairing.

Name: Ariane5_tank
Title: Ariane 5 EPC
Description: The EPC is the main stage of Ariane 5. It's a huge fuel tank.

Name: Sylda
Title: Ariane 5 SYLDA
Description: A system to place 2 payloads in the Ariane 5 fairing.

Name: Ariane4Fairing
Title: Ariane 3/4 fairing
Description: A fairing to protect the payload.

Name: Ariane5_RadialDecoupler
Title: Ariane 5 radial decoupler
Description: A radial decoupler to jettison EAP (SRB).

Name: Vega_Stage2
Title: Vega Stage 2 (Zefiro 23)
Description: The second stage of Vega is also a solid fuel booster.

Name: Ariane5_FairingSmall
Title: Ariane 5 small fairing
Description: A small fairing for small payloads.

Name: Ariane4Decoupler2
Title: Ariane 3/4 decoupler (2nd stage)
Description: Just a stack decoupler with tiny retro-SRBs.

Name: Ariane5_EPS
Title: Ariane 5 EPS
Description: The EPS is the second stage of the Ariane 5.

Name: Ariane4Decoupler1
Title: Ariane 3/4 decoupler (1st stage)
Description: Just a stack decoupler with tiny retro-SRBs.

Name: Ariane6_Stage3
Title: H30
Description: The H30 is powered by the Vinci engine and contains approximately 30 t of propellant. It is intended to serve as the upper stage of Ariane 6.

Name: Vega_Stage4
Title: Vega Stage 4 (AVUM)
Description: The Vega upper stage is a liquid fuel engine.

Name: DecouplerSylda
Title: Ariane 5 SYLDA Decoupler
Description: A stack decoupler for payloads releasing.

Name: FASAApollo_SM
Title: Apollo Service Module with RCS
Description: The Apollo Service Module. Contains fuel, RCS, ECS, fuel cell, and batteries. This has RCS pods built in.

Name: FASALM_LandingLegStaircase
Title: Apollo Lunar Module Leg - Ladder
Description: The landing leg with ladder.

Name: FASALM_LandingLegs
Title: Apollo Lunar Module Leg
Description: A landing leg with contact sensor.

Name: FASALM_AscentStage
Title: Apollo Lunar Module Ascent Module
Description: Apollo Ascent Module. Contains two astronauts.

Name: FASAGerminiSRB175
Title: UA1205 SRM
Description: Strap-on booster for Titan IIIC, IIID, IIIE, proposed for Saturn IB derivatives. Burn time 115s. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FASALM_DescentStage
Title: Apollo Lunar Module Descent Module
Description: This part contains fuel for landing, experiments, and importantly legs to set down softly.

Name: FASAApollo_SM_RCS
Title: Apollo Service Module RCS Quad Pod
Description: This is the RCS Quad Pods for the Apollo Service Module. Each contains it's own pressurization and fuel. Place 4 pods 90 degrees apart. 2:1 O/F Ratio.

Name: FASAApollo_SM_Dish
Title: Apollo Service Module High Gain Antenna
Description: The steerable unified S-band high-gain antenna for communication between Earth, the CSM, and the LM.

Name: FASAApollo_SM_Light
Title: Apollo Service Module Docking Light
Description: An extending light to provide some illumination for critical manoeuvres.

Name: FASALM_LandingLegsSA
Title: Apollo Lunar Module Leg - Surface Attach
Description: A surface attachable LEM landing leg with contact sensor.

Name: FASAALSEP_Scanner
Title: Apollo Lunar Module ALSEP Scanner
Description: SURFACE ONLY. Apollo science. Conduct your experiment while unit is still attached on lander. Requires KAS plugin to be deployed.

Name: FASASaturnSLA_med
Title: Spacecraft Lunar Module Adapter - Med Base
Description: This part is the Spacecraft Lunar Module Adapter base used to cover the Lunar Module during ascent.  It is fitted with two separate decouplers.  One separates the CSM through staging.  The other separates the LEM manually.  No extra decoupler is needed.  This is a slightly longer (2.6m) version to partially negate the collider issue with the LEM and IU while still maintaining the same basic height of the SLA.

Name: FASAApollo_LES
Title: Apollo Launch Escape System
Description: The LEA provides the means for separation the CM from the launch vehicle during pad or suborbital aborts. This assembly consists of a Q-ball instrumentation assembly, ballast compartment, canard surfaces, pitch control motor, tower jettison motor, launch escape motor, a structural skirt, an open-frame tower, and a boost protective cover.

Name: FASAApalloLFTF1Plate
Title: Saturn C-8 Second Stage
Description: The second stage for the Saturn C-8 launch vehicle.  Attach 8 J-2 engines.

Name: FASAALSEP_Device
Title: Passive Seismic Experiment Package (PSEP)
Description: Self supporting equipment to measure moonquakes in a passive manner. Requires KAS plugin to be deployed.

Name: FASALM_Antenna
Title: Apollo Lunar Module Antennas
Description: Just antennas, good for communicating. Place on top of the ascent stage.

Name: FASALM_DescentEngine
Title: Lunar Module Descent Engine
Description: Deeply throttleable pressure-fed vacuum engine used for the descent module of the Apollo lunar lander. Uses storable propellants which are not subject to boiloff, but are far less efficient than hydrolox or even kerolox. The version used on J-class missions had slightly higher specific impulse (this, along with other changes, gave enough payload capacity for the rover, for example). A later variant (TR-201) was used on Delta as an upper stage engine (on Delta P series); this was a low-cost model with more restarts (4 instead of 2) and slightly higher thrust but lower efficiency and no throttling capability. Diameter: [1.5 m]. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FASA_RO_UA1564
Title: UA1564 SRM
Description: Strap-on booster for uprated Titan 3 and Saturn INT / MLV applications.  Burn time 101s or 157s, depending on configuration chosen Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FASA_RO_UA1563
Title: UA1563 SRM
Description: Strap-on booster for uprated Titan 3 and Saturn INT / MLV applications.  Burn time 101s or 157s, depending on configuration chosen Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FASAApolloStrS1BPlate
Title: Engine Mount
Description: Engine mounting part for multiple engines.

Name: FASAStrFairing3m4x
Title: Spacecraft Lunar Module Adapter - Fairing
Description: This part, placed in a set of 4 covers the Apollo Lunar Module during ascent.

Name: FASAGeminiROTitanIIGLVUpper
Title: Titan II GLV Upper Stage Fuel Tank
Description: This propellant tank represents the tank used on the Titan II Gemini Launch Vehicle. It provides 8 more seconds of burn time via an extra ton of propellant.

Name: FASAALSEP_Reflector
Title: Laser Ranging Retroreflector (LRRR)
Description: Lunar Laser Ranging Experiment. A specialized retroreflector for allowing distance measurement from the Earth to the Moon. Requires KAS plugin to be deployed.

Name: FASALM_AscentEngine
Title: Lunar Module Ascent Engine
Description: Pressure-fed engine used for the ascent module of the Apollo lunar lander. Diameter: [0.86 m]. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FASAApollo_DockingDevice
Title: Apollo Docking Mechanism Probe
Description: Apollo Command Module Docking Probe. Will only work with the Apollo Lunar Module Drogue.

Name: FASASaturnSLA
Title: Spacecraft Lunar Module Adapter - Base
Description: This part is the Spacecraft Lunar Module Adapter base used to cover the Lunar Module during ascent.  It is fitted with two separate decouplers.  One separates the CSM through staging.  The other separates the LEM manually.  No extra decoupler is needed.

Name: FASAGeminiLegsX1
Title: FASA Advanced Gemini Landing Leg
Description: Need something to put a foot down, attach some of these and you won't have to crumple that cool spaceship.

Name: FASALM_StairCase
Title: Apollo Lunar Module Staircase
Description: A generic ladder for any need.

Name: FASA_Gemini_Lander_Eng
Title: FASA Advanced Gemini Lander Engine
Description: The main engine for the Gemini Lander. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FASALM_OutputPlace
Title: Apollo Lunar Module Mobility Enhancer
Description: A walkway to get from the door to the ladder.

Name: FASAGeminiEngineFuel2
Title: FASA Advanced Gemini Equipment Section
Description: This equipment section models the thrusters as an engine, rather than as RCS. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FASAGeminiEngFuelDescent
Title: FASA Advanced Gemini Descent Pack
Description: This pack contains an engine and more fuel for a Gemini based lander. Attach this as a descent stage to the Gemini for landings. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FASASaturnSLA_long
Title: Spacecraft Lunar Module Adapter - Long Base
Description: This part is the Spacecraft Lunar Module Adapter base used to cover the Lunar Module during ascent.  It is fitted with two separate decouplers.  One separates the CSM through staging.  The other separates the LEM manually.  No extra decoupler is needed.  This is a longer (3m) version to negate the collider issue with the LEM and IU.

Name: FASA_Apollo_Float_Round
Title: Float Spheres
Description: Floats spheres for water landings. They have a high heat resistance and impact rating for use as aero breaks and airbags.

Name: FASA_Apollo_Float_Ring
Title: Float Rings 2.5m
Description: Water floats for your 2.5m Command Module. Place in 4x symmetry and deploy just after splashdown.

Name: FASAGeminiDecDark375
Title: FASA Dark Decoupler [Large]
Description: A large sized dark decoupler for all your decoupling needs.

Name: FASAGeminiLFECentarTwin
Title: AJ10-138
Description: This can be an upper stage / orbital taxi for various Titan III configurations. Uses 2x AJ10-138. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FASALM_DecouplerRing
Title: Apollo Lunar Module Stage Separator
Description: This part splits the Ascent Module and Descent Module into two.  Hope you remembered everything, you won't be going back this trip.

Name: FASALM_RCS
Title: Apollo Lunar Module RCS Quad Pod
Description: A RCS thruster pod, set at 45 degree angles to make it more useful. RCS O/F Ratio 1.6:1.

Name: FASAGerminiSRB175_5Seg
Title: UA1204 SRM
Description: Earliest UA120 series booster designed. Designed for Titan booster augmentation for DynaSoar. Candidate for various Saturn INT studies. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FASA_Gemini_Lander_Leg_Part
Title: FASA Advanced Gemini Lander Leg
Description: Lander leg for the Gemini one man lander.

Name: FASAGeminiLegsX1White
Title: FASA Advanced Gemini Landing Leg
Description: Need something to put a foot down, attach some of these and you won't have to crumple that cool spaceship.

Name: FASAApalloLFTJ25XPlate
Title: Saturn S-II Stage
Description: The S-II stage as found on the Saturn V. Attach 5 Rocketdyne J-2 engines and the aft interstage to the bottom.

Name: FASAGeminiMiniSRB
Title: Gemini Retro Solid Rocket Motor
Description: Nice tiny solid rocket motor, designed to work with others and bring Gemini safely home again. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FASAGeminiNoseCone2Cap
Title: Gemini Nose Fairing
Description: A nose fairing to protect the fragile equipment contained in the rendezvous and recovery section during launch.

Name: FASA_Gemini_Lander_Pod
Title: Gemini Lightweight Lander
Description: Gemini Lander Pod. Contains one astronaut.

Name: FASAGeminiPodLight
Title: Gemini Light Pod
Description: Can't see, put one of these on. Problem solved.

Name: FASA_Gemini_Lander_Legs
Title: Gemini Lander Legs
Description: Lander legs for the Gemini one man lander

Name: FASAApalloLFTJ2Plate
Title: Saturn S-IVB Stage
Description: The S-IVB stage as found on the Saturn series. The Rocketdyne J-2 Rocket Engine and aft interstage attach to this part.

Name: FASAGeminiPod2White
Title: Gemini Cabin - White
Description: The Gemini cabin.  Contains two astronauts.  This one is made of new lightweight material and painted white to increase efficiency for rescue operations.

Name: FASAApolloLFEF1
Title: F-1 Series
Description: The massive Rocketdyne F-1 engine. One of the largest, most powerful rocket engines ever built. Ensure you enable roll capability or disable gimbal as required for your application. Diameter: [3.61 m]. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FASAGeminiAntenna
Title: Gemini Antenna
Description: This antenna is meant to be mounted on the Gemini rendezvous and recovery section.

Name: FASAGeminiNoseCone2White
Title: Gemini Rendezvous and Recovery Section Fairing
Description: This section contains all the necessary equipment for rendezvous and docking with the Agena Target Vehicle. After re-entry this section is jettisoned with deployment of the drogue parachute, after which the main parachute can then be deployed. Made of new lightweight material and painted white to match the white rescue Gemini pod.

Name: ExSmallGearBay
Title: Gemini Extra Small Gear Bay
Description: High performance tiny gear designed for atmospheric use.

Name: FASAGerminiSRBInlineSep
Title: In-Line Separation Motor
Description: A in-line separation motor for the Titan III Solid rocket boosters. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FASAAgenaDocking
Title: Gemini Agena Target/Docking Adapter
Description: Gemini target/docking adapter used to convert an Agena-D into a Gemini Agena Target Vehicle. Better put a fairing on it too.

Name: FASAGeminiUtilitySasRcs
Title: Gemini Adapter Retrograde Section
Description: The Gemini Adapter Retrograde Section. Contains the retrograde engines to de-orbit Gemini. Also houses RCS for translation up/down/left/right/aft. Modelled with the 2 backwards firing thrusters as well. RCS O/F Ratio 1.3:1.  Provides approximately 106dV for re-entry burn. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FASAApolloLFEM1
Title: M-1 Series
Description: The massive M-1 engine. The largest, most powerful, LH2/LOX engine ever designed. Individual components have been tested. Generally designed as an upper stage engine, first stages designs with expanding nozzles were being worked on. Diameter: [4.28 m]. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FASAGeminiUtilityPack
Title: Gemini Adapter Equipment Section
Description: The Gemini Adapter Equipment Section.  It contains O2 and H2 for fuel cell consumption and life support.  It also contains fuel for manoeuvring and attitude control thrusters.  This is the configuration as found on Gemini 10+. RCS O/F Ratio 1.3:1.

Name: FASAGeminiSasRcs
Title: FASA Gemini RCS Section
Description: This IMAGINARY Gemini RCS Section houses RCS for translation up/down/left/right/aft. Modelled with the 2 backwards firing thrusters as well. RCS O/F Ratio 1.3:1.

Name: FASAGerminiSRB175White
Title: UA1205 SRM
Description: Strap-on booster for Titan IIC, IIID, IIIE, proposed for Saturn IB derivatives. Burn time 115s. Painted white. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FASAGeminiPod2
Title: Gemini Cabin
Description: The Gemini cabin.  Contains two astronauts.

Name: FASA_Gemini_RCS_Thrusters
Title: Gemini RCS Thruster Pack
Description: Gemini thrusters go on the bottom of your Gemini adapter equipment section. They only thrust laterally, Left and Right. RCS O/F Ratio 1.3:1.

Name: FASAFairingBase_76m
Title: 396" PLF Base/Decoupler
Description: This 396" PLF (payload launch fairing) base is for Saturn V-sized payloads

Name: FASAGeminiPod2RCSWhite
Title: Gemini Re-entry Control System - White
Description: This section contains fuel and thrusters to provide Gemini 3 axis attitude control after detaching the adapter section. Made of new lightweight material and painted white to match the white rescue Gemini pod. RCS O/F Ratio 1.3:1.

Name: FASAGeminiParachute2D
Title: Gemini Recovery Drogue Parachute
Description: The Gemini recovery drogue parachute. Put this on top of the main parachute.  May be attached radially.

Name: FASAAtlasSLV3C
Title: Atlas SLV-3C/D Fuel Tank
Description: The fuel tank for the Atlas SLV-3C/D. Historically used with the Centaur D1 to send 1.75T (3C) or 1.80T (3D) to GTO.  Reduce fuel by 3t to setup the earlier 3C. (PART NOT COSTED BY RP-0 BUT IN CORRECT NODE)

Name: FASAGeminiParachute2
Title: Gemini Recovery Main Parachute
Description: The Gemini recovery main parachute. Put this on top of the RCS Control section.  May be attached radially.

Name: FASAGeminiNoseCone2
Title: Gemini Rendezvous and Recovery Section Fairing
Description: This section contains all the necessary equipment for rendezvous and docking with the Agena Target Vehicle. After re-entry jettison this section to deploy the drogue parachute, after which the main parachute can then be deployed as well.

Name: FASAGeminiNoseCone2Aero
Title: Big Gemini Aerodynamic Nose Fairing
Description: Since the rendezvous electronics are not needed with Big Gemini this recovery section is a bit more aerodynamic than before. Jettison this before deploying the parachutes.

Name: FASAGeminiBigGDec
Title: Big Gemini Decoupler
Description: A lighter decoupler for Big G.

Name: FASA_Gemini_Lander_LFT
Title: FASA Advanced Gemini Lander LFT
Description: The liquid fuel tanks from the lander as its own part for custom creations. Use with the Gemini Lander Engine.

Name: FASAGeminiPod2RCS
Title: Gemini Re-entry Control System
Description: This section contains fuel and thrusters to provide Gemini 3 axis attitude control after detaching the adapter section. RCS O/F Ratio 1.3:1.

Name: FASAAtlasSLV3A
Title: Atlas SLV-3A Fuel Tank
Description: The fuel tank for the Atlas SLV-3A launcher.  Extended fuel tank for larger payloads.

Name: FASAGeminiBigGDockExt
Title: Big Gemini Docking Ring
Description: Extendible docking ring for the Big G science lab.

Name: FASAGeminiLES
Title: Big Gemini Launch Escape System (LES)
Description: A launch escape system for use with Big Gemini. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FASAGeminiBigG
Title: Big Gemini Passenger Compartment
Description: This is the lower half of the Big Gemini re-entry module, the passenger compartment.  This module gives the Big G a max 9 person crew capacity with additional cargo space.

Name: FASAGeminiBigGWhite
Title: Big Gemini Passenger Compartment - White
Description: This is the lower half of the Big Gemini re-entry module, the passenger compartment.  This version is made of new lightweight materials and painted white for rescue operations.  It has less cargo space but can support up to 12 person crew, including the flight compartment.

Name: FASA_BigGeminiParachute2
Title: Big Gemini Recovery Main Parachute
Description: The Big Gemini parachute. Put this on top of the RCS Control section when making Big Gemini (instead of the regular Gemini parachute).

Name: FASABigGeminiRetroModule
Title: Big Gemini Retro Module
Description: The Big Gemini Retro Module that contains 4x solid rockets to de-orbit Big Gemini. Decouples before re-entry.  Provides approximately 106dV for re-entry burn.

Name: FASAGeminiBigGDock
Title: Big Gemini Service Module
Description: The service module and cargo storage for the Big Gemini spacecraft. Decouples before re-entry burn.

Name: FASAApolloStrS1BPlateNova
Title: Engine Mount
Description: Engine mounting part for multiple engines.

Name: FASAFairingsApolloPlate375m
Title: Big Gemini Decoupler [260"]
Description: This 260" decoupler is for S-IVB sized payloads like Big Gemini.

Name: WingGeminiFPContSurf
Title: Gemini Winged Flight Pack Control Surface
Description: It's not really a control surface, its more of a metal slat that deflects some of the air that goes by. Goes on the Gemini Flight Pack over the holes...

Name: FASAApolloStrJ2StrJ25mDec
Title: Saturn S-II Aft Interstage - Top
Description: This part is the top part of the Saturn S-II stage aft interstage aboard the Saturn V launch vehicle.

Name: FASAApolloStrJ2Fairing
Title: Saturn S-IVB Stage Aft Interstage
Description: This part is the aft interstage for the S-IVB aboard the Saturn S-IB Launch Vehicle.

Name: FASAApolloStrJ2StrJ23m5mDec
Title: Saturn S-IVB Stage Aft Interstage
Description: This part is the aft interstage for the S-IVB when used with the Saturn V.

Name: FASAGeminiLFTLonger
Title: Titan 3 Series Fuel Tank
Description: This fuel tank can be used for the lower stage in Titan 3BS/34D series builds.

Name: FASAStrF1Fairing
Title: Saturn V Engine Fairing
Description: Fairing cone designed to shield the powerful F-1 engines.

Name: FASA_Mercury_Eng
Title: Mercury Retro Rocket Pack
Description: This pack contains 3 solid rocket engines to de-orbit the Mercury capsule. They are each 1000lbf (4.448kN) and burn for 10 seconds and are fired at five second intervals, thus peak thrust is 8.9kN). Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FASAApollo_SM_Engine
Title: AJ10-137 (Service Propulsion System)
Description: The Aerojet AJ10-137 rocket engine used on the Apollo Service Module as the Service Propulsion System. Diameter: [3.9 m]. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FASAGerminiSRB175_7Seg
Title: UA1206 SRM
Description: Strap-on booster for Titan 34D. Burn time 114s. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FASAApalloLFTS1BStage1
Title: Saturn S-IB Stage Tanks
Description: This is the fuel/oxidizer tanks assembly for the S-IB found on the Saturn IB.

Name: WingGemini
Title: Gemini Wings
Description: The Winged Gemini experiment was designed so that Gemini could land on a runway. It would have greatly reduced the cost of recovery, but it was so unstable and hard to control in tests that it was abandoned.  See if you can do better! Make sure you come in nose first, if you start to spin turn off SAS and you will eventually recover, maybe. Also you will have very little control until you get to the thicker part of the atmosphere keep it nose down as long as possible to keep your speed up. Your glide slope should be very steep.

Name: FASAGeminiLFTCentarCSM_D1T
Title: Centaur D-1T
Description: Tank and thrust structure for the Centaur D1T models. Used on the Titan III-E. Add one or two RL10A series engines to complete the stage.

Name: WingGeminiFP
Title: Gemini Winged Flight Pack
Description: Decoupler, and SAS flight pack for Winged Gemini.  This pack has a decoupler on the bottom to jettison spent fuel tanks or engines.

Name: WingGeminiContSurf
Title: Gemini Winged Control Surface
Description: Helps Gemini fly!  Put two of these stubby little control surfaces on the bottom of the Gemini wing.

Name: FASAApollo_CM_Top
Title: Apollo Command Module Forward Heat Shield
Description: This heat shield protects the earth landing (recovery) system components and everything else in the forward compartment.

Name: FASAApollo_CM_HeatShield
Title: Apollo Command Module Heat Shield
Description: This part is the ablative heat shield for the Apollo Command Module.

Name: FASAApollo_CM_parachutes
Title: Apollo Command Module Main Parachutes
Description: The three main recovery parachutes for the Apollo Command Module.

Name: FASAApollo_CM_Decoupler
Title: Apollo Command/Service Module Decoupler
Description: This part separates the Command Module from the Service Module.

Name: FASALM_DockingCone
Title: Apollo Docking Mechanism Drogue
Description: Apollo Lunar Module Docking Drogue. Will only works with the Apollo Command Module Probe.

Name: FASAApalloLFTJ2Nova
Title: Saturn C-8 First Stage
Description: An extremely large liquid fuel tank for the first stage of the Saturn C-8 launch vehicle. 50ft Diameter.  Attach 8 F-1 engines.

Name: FASAApollo_CM
Title: Apollo Command Module
Description: Apollo Command Module. Contains three astronauts.

Name: FASAApolloIU
Title: Saturn IB/V Instrument Unit
Description: The Saturn Instrument Unit provides command and control for the final stages of the Saturn IB/V series vehicles. Could be used with any other 260" launch vehicles.

Name: FASAApolloStrJ2StrJ23m5mDecNova
Title: Saturn C-8 Interstage
Description: An interstage separating the first and second stage of the Saturn C-8 launch vehicle. 33ft to 50ft Diameter.

Name: FASAMercuryAtlasLFTLong
Title: Atlas SLV-3 Fuel Tank
Description: The fuel tank for the Atlas SLV-3 launcher. Used with the Gemini Agena Target Vehicle.

Name: FASAStrS1BWing
Title: Saturn S-IB Fin
Description: A fin to help stabilize the Saturn IB.

Name: FASAFairingNosecone_3mSRB
Title: Nose Fairing [120" UA120X SRM]
Description: A 120" nose fairing for all your UA120X SRM needs. Includes a separation motor. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FASADeltaAv2
Title: Delta Avionics Unit
Description: Avionics unit for the Extended Long Tank Thor and Extra Extended Long Tank Thor rocket stages. Delta I and Delta II.

Name: FASAGeminiLFTMedWhite
Title: Titan II/III/IV Series Upper Stage Fuel Tank
Description: This fuel tank can be used for the upper stage in Titan 23G, Titan III series, and Titan IV series builds. Also includes a radio guidance module.

Name: FASAGeminiLFTMed
Title: Titan II Upper Stage Fuel Tank
Description: This propellant tank represents the tank used on the Titan II ICBM.

Name: FASAGeminiMOLEquip
Title: Manned Orbital Lab (MOL) Cargo Bay
Description: This equipment module is a part of the Manned Orbital Laboratory. Contains storage space for equipment, fuel tanks and small probes.

Name: FASAApolloDecSV5m
Title: Saturn S-II Aft Interstage - Bottom
Description: This part is the bottom part of the Saturn S-II stage aft interstage aboard the Saturn V launch vehicle.

Name: FASAGeminiMOLEquipStack
Title: Manned Orbital Lab (MOL) Cargo Bay - Stack
Description: This is a stackable version of the MOL Equipment Module that allows for a larger storage bay.

Name: FASAApalloLFTSVS1
Title: Saturn S-IC Stage
Description: The S-IC stage as found on the Saturn V. Attach 5 Rocketdyne F-1 engines and 4 fairings to the bottom of the stage.

Name: FASAGeminiMOLSci
Title: Manned Orbital Lab (MOL) Science Module
Description: Planned crewed orbiting laboratory for the US Air Force (with secret orbital photographic reconaissance mission).

Name: FASAApolloAPS
Title: Saturn IB/V - APS Flight Pack
Description: This unique engine/RCS combo even comes with a little bit of fuel. Great for probes and control motors. RCS O/F Ratio 1.63:1. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FASAFairingsPlate375m
Title: Payload Launch Fairing Base [Large]
Description: A large payload launch fairing base for all your fairing needs.

Name: FASAGeminiLFTLong
Title: Titan II Series Fuel Tank
Description: This fuel tank can be used for the lower stage in both Titan II ICBM and Titan II Gemini Launch Vehicle builds.

Name: FASASaturnUllage
Title: S-II Ullage Rocket
Description: Attaches to the upper part of the S-II interstage, in sets of 4 to 8. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FASAGeminiDecDark25_Titan3m
Title: Titan Decoupler [120"]
Description: Decoupler for Titan II/III/IV Series rockets and other 120" Parts

Name: FASAFairingBase_43m
Title: Payload Launch Fairing Expanded Base [168"]
Description: A 168" PLF (payload launch fairing) base is for Titan IIIE and Commercial Titan III payloads.

Name: FASAApalloLFTSVS2
Title: Saturn Fuel Tank
Description: A fuel tank with Saturn type markings.

Name: FASA_SIB
Title: Saturn S-IB Stage
Description: This part is the fuel/oxidizer tanks and thrust structure for the S-IB found on the Saturn IB. Attach 8 Rocketdyne H-1 engines and 8 fins to the bottom of the stage.

Name: FASAGeminiMOLEquipCap
Title: Manned Orbital Lab (MOL) Cargo Bay - Cap
Description: This cap goes on either end of MOL Equipment Module stack to complete the module.

Name: FASAExplorerProbe
Title: Explorer 1 Probe
Description: Explorer 1, the first satellite launched by the United States, was a very simple scientific probe of less than a dozen kilograms. It featured a cosmic ray detector and micrometeorite detectors, as well as temperature sensors. Mercury batteries provided a month of electricity for the high power transmitter and another two and a half months for the low-power transmitter.

Name: FASAProbeParachute
Title: Mercury Parachute Mini
Description: The Mini Parachute is a lot weaker than the standard one and useless for anything heavier than a probe core. DO NOT USE ON LIVE SUBJECTS!!!!

Name: FASA_RO_UA1207
Title: UA1207 SRM
Description: Strap-on booster for Titan 3M. Burn time 117s. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FASAExplorerNosecone
Title: Juno I Nosecone Fairing & Instrument Section
Description: Nosecone and Instrument Section for the Juno I first stage, has a decoupler on the nose. Separates from fuel tank after first stage burnout.

Name: FASAApolloLFEH1
Title: H-1/RS-27 Series
Description: The H-1 is an upgrade to the LR79 engine that propelled the Saturn-I and IB vehicles, as well as late-model Delta rockets (as the RS-27). The H-1/RS-27 are optimized for the first-stage main engine role. The RS-27A has a higher expansion ratio for increased performance at altitude since liftoff thrust on the Delta II is augmented by solid boosters and the core burns rather longer. Diameter: [1.0 m]. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FASAlaunchTower
Title: FASA Launch Tower
Description: This launch tower lets you load Kerbals from the tower to your spacecraft.  Load it up with Kerbals from the astronaut complex and right click on the doors at the top or bottom to EVA.

Name: FASAGeminiDecDark25
Title: FASA Dark Decoupler [Medium]
Description: A medium sized dark decoupler for all your decoupling needs.

Name: FASAGeminiDecDark125_Redstone
Title: Mercury - Redstone Spacecraft Adapter
Description: Spacecraft adapter coupler for Mercury - Redstone Launch Vehicle

Name: FASAExplorerLFTLong
Title: Juno I Tank
Description: A stretched Redstone tank for Jupiter-C / Juno I. Fill with LOX/Hydyne for use with NAA75-110 engine in LOX/Hydyne mode.

Name: FASAMercruyCap2
Title: Mercury Nose Fairing
Description: This nose fairing protects the parachute during flight.

Name: FASAExplorerSgt3
Title: Baby Sergeant 3x Solid Kick Motor Cluster
Description: Middle cluster in Sergeant Cluster used on Juno I and II launch vehicles and on the Jupiter-C test rocket. Uses the high performance variant (JPL-532A). Attaches below 3x decoupler. Attach 11x decoupler below this. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FASAAgenaLFT_b
Title: Agena-B Propellant Tank
Description: Propellant tanks for the Agena-B.

Name: FASAAgena_Engine_FP_b
Title: Agena-B Flight Pack
Description: Flight Pack RCS for Agena-B and BAC Model 8081 engine.

Name: FASADeltaAv1
Title: Thor/Delta Avionics Unit
Description: Early 2.44m avionics unit for Long Tank Thor and Long Tank Thrust Augmented Thor rocket stage.  Delta L-N and Delta 0.

Name: FASA_Atlas_LFT_Cone2
Title: Atlas-E/F Fuel Tank
Description: The fuel tank for the Atlas-E/F series.

Name: FASAMercuryAtlasEng
Title: LR105 Series
Description: Kerolox gas-generator sustainer engine used in the Atlas launch vehicle. It, like the Atlas's booster engines (LR89s) are lit on the ground, but after a bit over 2 minutes' flight the boosters are dropped and the Atlas core continues to orbit under the power of the sustainer engine (and the verniers for roll control and final adjustment). The final configuration of the LR105 (like the LR89) uses RS-27 components for increased performance. As a sustainer engine, the LR105 has relatively poor sea level specific impulse compared to most boosters, but somewhat better vacuum specific impulse--though the difference in both is nowhere near as pronounced as when comparing a booster to an upper stage engine. Diameter: [1.5 m]. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FASAGeminiLFT_TitanIV
Title: Titan IV Series Fuel Tank
Description: This fuel tank can be used for the lower stage in Titan IV series builds.

Name: FASAMercuryDec
Title: Mercury Retro Strap / Decoupler
Description: Straps to hold retro pack to heatshield (place on heatshield, then add retro pack). Decouple before re-entry.

Name: FASAFairingBase_15m
Title: Payload Launch Fairing Base [60"]
Description: A 60" PLF (payload launch fairing) base for Atlas and Agena-D payloads.

Name: FASADeltaMB3LFE
Title: LR79 Series
Description: Long-lasting US Kerolox gas-generator booster engine. The same components and broadly the same performance as the LR89, the LR79 (also known as S-3D in Jupiter / Juno II) powered Jupiter, Thor, and Thor-Delta (Delta) rockets. Diameter: [1.53 m]. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FASAMercuryAtlasEngBooster
Title: LR89 Series
Description: Kerolox gas-generator engine that served as booster for Atlas. Late model LR89s were upgraded with RS-27 components for higher efficiency. Very similar to LR79 (this was the pure-booster variant). Diameter: [1.0 m]. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FASAExplorerSgt3Dec
Title: Baby Sergeant 3x Cluster Decoupler
Description: A small decoupler for your 3x Baby Sargent engine cluster.

Name: FASAExplorerSgt11
Title: Baby Sergeant 11x Solid Kick Motor Cluster
Description: First stage in the Sergeant Cluster used on Juno I and II launch vehicles and on the Jupiter-C test rocket. Uses T17-E2 fuel mixture, with lower performance than the JPL-532A fuel in the third and fourth stages. Attaches to the Baby Sergeant 11x decoupler. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FASAExplorerSgt11Dec
Title: Baby Sergeant 11x Cluster Decoupler
Description: A light decoupler for your Baby Sergeant 11x cluster. This attaches to the top of the Sergeant 3x rocket.

Name: FASA_Mercury_LFT_Long
Title: Mercury - Redstone LV Fuel Tank
Description: The fuel tank for the Mercury - Redstone Launch Vehicle. Used for sub-orbital flights.

Name: FASA_Gemini_ASAS_Comp
Title: Remote Control Unit
Description: Add to a spacecraft to add autonomous operation for testing without risking the life of a Kerbal.

Name: NP_lfe_25m_Orbitalbertha_Mini
Title: XLR99 Spaceplane Engine
Description: LOX/Ammonia gas generator engine which powered the X-15 spaceplane. The first large, throttleable, restartable liquid fuel rocket engine. Diameter: [1.42 m]. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FASAApalloLFTJ2
Title: Saturn Fuel Tank
Description: A fuel tank with Saturn type markings.

Name: FASAMercuryPod
Title: Mercury Re-entry Module
Description: The Mercury re-entry module.  Contains one astronaut.  Built in RCS thrusters.

Name: FASAFairingBase_508m
Title: Payload Launch Fairing Expanded Base [200"]
Description: A 200" PLF (payload launch fairing) base for Titan IV payloads.

Name: FASAMercuryPodRCS
Title: Mercury RCS Roll Thruster Pack
Description: Mercury roll control thrusters.  Put 1 pack on right side of spacecraft at height of lowest part of hatch.

Name: FASAMercuryMiniSRB
Title: Mercury Posigrade Solid Rocket Motor
Description: A tiny solid rocket motor, designed to separate Mercury spacecraft from its booster. Mount in a set of three to the Mercury retropack and stage along with the Atlas or Redstone decoupler. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FASAGeminiLFTCentarCSM_D2
Title: Centaur D2
Description: Tank and thrust structure for the Centaur II and IIAS models. Used on the Atlas II and IIIA. Add one or two RL10A series engines to complete the stage. (PART NOT COSTED BY RP-0 BUT IN CORRECT NODE)

Name: FASAExplorerSgt
Title: Baby Sergeant (5.4KS1975)
Description: A small solid kick motor used on the Jupiter-C sounding rocket (and later the Juno I and II launch vehicles) as upper stages in clusters of 11, 3 and, finally, one attached to the payload. The standard version uses the T17-E2 grain mixture while the higher performance one uses the JPL-532A. Very low overall performance and reliability. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FASAGeminiLFTShortWhite
Title: FASA Fuel Tank
Description: A generic fuel tank.

Name: FASAMercuryFairing
Title: Atlas Fairing Decoupler
Description: Part of the MA-2/3/5 Propulsion Unit, this is a decoupler/fairing for the booster engines of Atlas. Place this on top of the main engines, then add the boosters.

Name: FASAlaunchClamp125
Title: Redstone and Juno I Launch Clamp
Description: This clamp attaches to the bottom of the A-7 Rocket Engine used in the Redstone-Mercury and Juno I launch vehicles.

Name: FASAApolloLFEJ2
Title: J-2 Series
Description: The Rocketdyne J-2 rocket engine found on the Saturn S-IVB and S-II stages. Ensure you enable roll capability or disable gimbal as required for your application. Diameter: [2.01 m]. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FASADeltaAv0
Title: Thor Avionics Unit
Description: Small, 1.5m avionics unit for Thor and Thrust Augmented Thor rocket stage.  Used on Thor-Able, Thor-Agena, Thor-Ablestar, Thor-Burner, Thor-Delta and early Delta rockets (A-K).

Name: FASADeltaAv4
Title: DCSS-5 Avionics Unit
Description: Integrated avionics unit for 5m Delta Cryogenic Second Stage and Delta IV-M/IV-HLV launch vehicle.

Name: FASADeltaAv3
Title: DCSS-4 Avionics Unit
Description: Integrated avionics unit for 4m Delta Cryogenic Second Stage and Delta III/IV-M launch vehicle.

Name: FASAFairingsCone3m
Title: Payload Launch Fairing Expanded Base [Large]
Description: A large expanded payload launch fairing base for all your fairing needs.

Name: FASAGeminiDecDark125
Title: FASA Dark Decoupler [Small]
Description: A small sized dark decoupler for all your decoupling needs.

Name: FASAFairingsPlate1m
Title: Payload Launch Fairing Base [Small]
Description: A small payload launch fairing base for all your fairing needs.

Name: FASA_Mercury_RCS_Short
Title: FASA Pressurized Fuel Tank
Description: A generic pressurized fuel tank.

Name: FASAFairingWall05m_agena
Title: Agena Bottom Fairing
Description: Place 2 on bottom area of agena above engine to cover flight pack.

Name: FASA_Mercury_Redstone_Eng
Title: NAA-75-110 A-Series
Description: Used on the Redstone missile.  Designed for Ethanol/LOx (A-6) (1.5 O/F Ratio), it was later adapted to burn Hydyne/LOx (A-7) (1.73 O/F Ratio)(higher performance (12%) yet more toxic) for use in Jupiter C / Juno I.  When Redstone MRLV was adapted from Jupiter C for manned use the A7 was switched back to Ethanol, accepting slightly lower performance for lack of toxicity. Thrust Vector Control was provided by carbon thrust vanes (add the Redstone Fin / Thrust vane part in 4x symmetry), and additional attitude control was provided by actuating fins. Mass includes thrust frame. Diameter: [1.77 m]. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FASAGemini4X800Mini
Title: XLR11
Description: While it doesn't look a thing like it, this model represents the Reaction Motors XLR11, the first liquid fueled rocket engine designed for airplanes. Powered the X-1. Diameter: [0.46 m]. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FASAAgenaProbe
Title: Agena Bus/Guidance Unit
Description: The Agena electronics and avionics package. Provides an 11.8 kWh battery, providing control for just over 47 hr, and an omnidirectional antenna with an effective range of 1,500 km to ground stations.

Name: FASAMercuryRedstoneFin
Title: A-7 Fin / Thrust Vane
Description: The Redstone / Jupiter-C / Juno engine could not gimbal.  Instead TVC was obtained by use of carbon thrust vanes. Apply in 4x symmetry to A7 engine unit.

Name: FASAProbeGeigerCounter
Title: Geiger Counter
Description: This Geiger counter measures gamma rays and stores that data for scientific study.

Name: GeminiNosecone625m
Title: Nose Fairing [Small]
Description: A small nose cone fairing for all your fairing needs.

Name: FASAFairingNosecone_4mSRB
Title: Nose Fairing [156" UA156X SRM]
Description: A 156" nose fairing for all your UA156X SRM needs. Includes a separation motor. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FASAAgena_Engine
Title: XLR81 (Agena) Vacuum Engine
Description: Gas-generator nitric acid/UDMH vacuum engine used on Agena. The XLR81 family was derived from the Bell Hustler Rocket Engine, which was developed for use on an air-to-surface missile. Early engines were nearly identical to the Hustler engine, while later variants offered new capabilities and improved performance. Engine restart was introduced on the Agena B's XLR81-BA-7 (Model 8081). The XLR81-BA-11 (Model 8096) used on Agena D used propellant sumps to eliminate the need for ullage thrust. The XLR81-BA-13 (Model 8247) powered the Gemini Agena Target Vehicle (a modified Agena D) and was rated for up to 14 restarts. Diameter: [0.9 m]. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: TitanIUpper
Title: Titan I Series Upper Stage Fuel Tank
Description: This fuel tank can be used for the upper stage in Titan I series builds. Also includes a radio guidance module.

Name: FASAGeminiLFTTitan1
Title: Titan 1 Series Fuel Tank
Description: This fuel tank can be used for the lower stage in Titan 1 series builds.

Name: FASA_Mercury_LFEng
Title: Storable Propellant Retro Pack (2kN class)
Description: This is the equivalent in thrust of two Generic 1kN thrusters. Pressure-fed from bladder tanks, effectively infinite ignitions and no ullage issues. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FASAFairingNosecone_6_6mSRB
Title: Nose Fairing [260" UA156X SRM]
Description: A 260" nose fairing for all your AJ-260 SRM needs. Includes a separation motor. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FASAFairingsCone1m
Title: Payload Launch Fairing Expanded Base [Medium]
Description: A medium expanded payload launch fairing base for all your fairing needs.

Name: GeminiNosecone1m
Title: Nose Fairing [Medium]
Description: A medium nose cone fairing for all your fairing needs.

Name: FASA_Mercury_Parachute_Box
Title: Mercury Parachute
Description: The Mercury recovery parachute. Sits on the capsule with the nose fairing on top of it.

Name: FASAGeminiLR91Mini
Title: LR91 Series
Description: The LR91 powered the second stage of Titan launchers. Exhaust from the gas generator provided roll control. Diameter: [2.9 m]. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FASAGeminiLR91
Title: LR91 Series
Description: The LR91 powered the second stage of Titan launchers. Exhaust from the gas generator provided roll control. Diameter: [2.9 m]. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FASAGeminiLFTCentarCSM_T
Title: Centaur T
Description: 4.32m Tank and thrust structure for the Centaur T used on the Titan IV. Add a single RL10A series engines to complete the stage. (PART NOT COSTED BY RP-0 BUT IN CORRECT NODE)

Name: FASATitanLR91Dec
Title: LR91 Decoupler
Description: Place this part under the LR91 for staging.

Name: FASAGeminiLR87Twin
Title: LR87 Booster
Description: Used in the first stage of the Titan rocket family, the LR87 is composed of two engines with separate turbomachinery integrated into one unit. The version used on Titan I burned kerosene and liquid oxygen, while Titan II through Titan IV burned storable propellants. A modified version burning liquid hydrogen was developed for the upper stages of Saturn V and Saturn IB, but the J-2 was selected instead. Diameter: [3.0 m]. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FASAFairingsPlate2m
Title: Payload Launch Fairing Base [Medium]
Description: A medium payload launch fairing base for all your fairing needs.

Name: GeminiNosecone2m
Title: Nose Fairing [Large]
Description: A large nose cone fairing for all your fairing needs.

Name: FASAFairingBase_165m
Title: Payload Launch Fairing Base [65"]
Description: A 65" PLF (payload launch fairing) base for Agena-D payloads.

Name: FASAlaunchClampAtlas
Title: FASA Atlas Launch Clamp
Description: The "Atlas Clamp" attaches to the sides of rockets to help stop the launch wiggles. This clamp works just like the stock launch clamps except they do not provide electricity.

Name: FASAAgenaAnt
Title: Agena-D Antenna
Description: An extendible antenna for the Agena-D.

Name: FASAAgena_Engine_FP_d
Title: Agena-D Flight Pack
Description: Flight Pack RCS (with no SPS) for Agena-D and BAC Model 8096/8247 engine.

Name: FASAAgena_Engine_FP
Title: Agena-D Flight Pack with SPS
Description: Flight Pack (RCS, SPS) for Agena-D and BAC Model 8096/8247 engine. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FASAAgenaLFT
Title: Agena-D Propellant Tank
Description: Propellant tanks for the Agena-D.

Name: FASA_Mercury_LFT_Short
Title: FASA Fuel Tank
Description: A generic fuel tank.

Name: FASAMercuryAtlasVernierEngine
Title: LR101 Series
Description: Pump or pressure-fed kerolox vernier engine. Used for attitude control and final velocity adjustment in the MA-x system (2x LR89 + LR105 + 2x LR101) on Atlas, and MB-x system (LR79 or RS-27 + 2xLR101) on Thor-Able / Thor-Agena / Thor-Delta / Delta. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FASAICBMProbe
Title: Titan II ICBM Guidance Package
Description: Delco Universal Space Guidance System (USGS).  Carousel IV IMU.  Magic 352 Computer.

Name: FASAICBMSAS
Title: Titan II Mk6 Re-Entry Vehicle Base
Description: This part is both the interface from the Titan II to the Mk6 Re-Entry Vehicle and the base of the Mk6 Re-Entry Vehicle itself.  It is modelled as simply the re-entry vehicle.

Name: FASAGeminiDecDark125_Atlas
Title: Mercury - Atlas Spacecraft Adapter
Description: Spacecraft adapter for the Mercury - Atlas Launch Vehicle.

Name: FASAGeminiLFTLongIF
Title: Titan 23G/3 Series Fuel Tank
Description: This fuel tank can be used for the lower stage in Titan 23G and Titan 3A/B/C/D/E series builds

Name: FASAFairingBase_3m
Title: Payload Launch Fairing Base [120"]
Description: A 120" PLF (payload launch fairing) base is for Titan II and III series payloads.

Name: FASA_Atlas_LFT_Cone
Title: Mercury - Atlas Launch Vehicle Fuel Tank
Description: The fuel tank for the Mercury - Atlas Launch Vehicle, aka Atlas D Mercury Launch Vehicle, aka Atlas LV-3B.

Name: FASAICBMMIRV
Title: W53 Warhead - 9MT
Description: The Titan II ICBM W53 Warhead.  Installed as a single warhead atop the Guidance Package.

Name: FASAGeminiLFTCentarCSM_D5
Title: Centaur D3
Description: Tank and thrust structure for the Centaur III used on the Atlas V. Add one or two RL10A series engines to complete the stage.  Includes integrated avionics for the full Atlas V launch vehicle. (PART NOT COSTED BY RP-0 BUT IN CORRECT NODE)

Name: FASAApolloLFERL10
Title: RL10 Series Vacuum Engine
Description: Hydrolox restartable expander-cycle vacuum engine used in multiple upper stages, including Centaur, the Saturn I S-IV, and the Delta Cryogenic Second Stage. It has low thrust, but very high specific impulse and low mass, making it ideal for high energy, beyond-low-Earth-orbit applications like launching satellites to geostationary transfer orbits or to the Moon or other planets. However, like all hydrolox engines, hydrogen boiloff is a serious issue without heat pumps or radiators. Diameter: [0.92 m]. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FASASolarMini
Title: FASA Solar Panel
Description: A nice small 0.05m^2 solar panel for small parts.

Name: FASADeltaCastorSrb
Title: Castor 1 Solid Rocket Motor
Description: A booster motor for the Delta D rocket. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FASAAtlasLV3C
Title: Atlas LV-3C Fuel Tank
Description: The fuel tank for the Atlas LV-3C. Historically used to loft the Centaur D1 into orbit, but has many uses.

Name: FASAGeminiLFTCentar
Title: Centaur A/B/C/D/D1
Description: Tank and thrust structure for the Centaur A/B/C/D/D1 models. Add two RL10A series engines to complete the stage.

Name: RO_Centaur_RCS
Title: Centaur Attitude Jet
Description: These thrusters are for roll control of the Centaur upper stage rocket.

Name: FASAlaunchClamp25
Title: Generic Launch Clamp
Description: A launch clamp that is resizable to match whatever you need.

Name: FASAUmbilicalTower
Title: FASA Umbilical Tower
Description: This umbilical tower functions as a launch clamp and fuel pump for liquid fuel, oxidizer and mono-propellent. It also Provides electricity. Right click on the tower to start the fuel flow.

Name: FASAAtlasH
Title: Atlas G/H/I Fuel Tank
Description: The fuel tank for the Atlas G/H/I. Historically used with the Centaur D1A to send up to 2.375T to GTO.

Name: FASA_Mercury_LES
Title: Mercury Launch Escape System
Description: Set up an action group to turn on the engine. Otherwise staging will just release it. Attach this to the top of your Mercury capsule, in case there is an emergency. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FASAlaunchClampApollo
Title: FASA Apollo Launch Clamp
Description: Similar to the clamps that held the Saturn V down while the engines spooled up. The clamp had a special hood it retracted into. It protect the clamps from rocket exhaust so they could be reused for multiple launches.

Name: FASAAtlasII
Title: Atlas II Fuel Tank
Description: The fuel tank for the Atlas II. Historically used with the Centaur D2 to send up to 3.8T to GTO.

Name: FASAFairingWall05m
Title: Fairing Wall Half [Small-Short]
Description: A small wall half, short length, for all your fairing needs.

Name: FASAE1
Title: E-1
Description: Pump-fed kerolox open cycle (gas generator) booster engine developed from LR79/89. Backup proposal for the first stage engine on the Titan 1 ICBM, and proposed first stage engine on the Saturn 1 but ultimately never flown (4 E-1s replaced with 8 H-1s). Diameter: [2.14 m]. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FSlancasterEngine
Title: Napier Sabre VII Piston Engine
Description: WWII-era H-24 liquid-cooled piston engine. Provides 3000HP at sea level (WEP), rated at 2800HP at 6km. Two-speed single stage automatic-switching supercharger. A development of the engine used on the Hawker Tempest.

Name: Griffon88
Title: Rolls-Royce Griffon 88 piston engine
Description: Rolls Royce Griffon 88. 2350HP sea level with a two stage two speed supercharger maintaining 2100HP to 5km.

Name: Griffon101
Title: Rolls-Royce Griffon 101 piston engine
Description: Rolls Royce Griffon 101. Two stage three speed supercharger (only two stages modeled, so it overperforms 1-3km). Rated 2420HP at 1.5km, 2250HP at 4.4km, and 2050HP at 6.4km. 11ft 5-blade constant speed propeller.

Name: Liberty12
Title: Liberty L-12
Description: Liberty V12 engine rated at 449HP at 2000RPM (max). 10ft 2-blade fixed pitch propeller.

Name: FSoblongTailJet
Title: General Electric J47-GE-27
Description: 1950s GE J47 Turbojet mounted in the tail section, as used in F-86F Sabre. 5.5 OPR, no afterburner. SFC of 0.902lb/lbf-hr. Max thrust 26.47kN.

Name: FSlancasterEngineGear
Title: Rolls-Royce Merlin XII (with gear)
Description: WWII-era V-12 liquid-cooled piston engine. Provides 1175HP at sea level, rising to 1290 at 3.4km (full throttle height). Single-speed single-stage supercharger. The engine used on the Spitfire IIa.

Name: DB-605-A
Title: Daimler-Benz DB 605 A
Description: WWII-era V-12 liquid-cooled piston engine, the DB-605 A as produced by Daimler-Benz (GER). Used on the Messerschmitt Bf 109 fighter. 1475PS.

Name: FSpropellerFolding
Title: AJE Folding Electric Propeller
Description: 500 horsepower, consumes about 400 EC/s

Name: V-1650-7
Title: Packard Merlin V-1650-7
Description: WWII-era V-12 liquid-cooled piston engine, the Merlin as produced by Packard (US). 1620HP at sea level with ram air with a very strong two-speed two-stage supercharger (1710 max with ram air at just over 3km, second peak 1410HP at 7.9km). 67inHG max boost. Used on the P-51B/C/D Mustang. 11ft 2in 4 blade constant speed propeller.

Name: FSnoseEngine
Title: Packard Merlin V-1650-9
Description: WWII-era V-12 liquid-cooled piston engine. 2160HP at sea level with ram air with a very strong automatic two-speed two-stage supercharger (2210HP max with ram air). 90inHG max boost. Used on the P-51H Mustang.

Name: FSswampEngine
Title: Swamp Propeller
Description: 600 HP piston engine and low-speed propeller

Name: BMWIIIa
Title: BMW IIIa
Description: WWI-era supercharged water-cooled straight six inline engine, rated at 230HP to 2km at 1400RPM (max). 9ft 2-blade fixed pitch propeller.

Name: FREFRE1
Title: FRE-1
Description: The Firefly Research Engine 1 (FRE-1) is an upper stage engine developped by Firefly, and intended to be used with the Firefly Alpha launch vehicle. It features a low production cost along a simple and efficient pressure-fed system. The Firefly engines will burn RP1 on the first flights, but they will be upgraded to burn Methane and therefore improve their efficiency. [1.3m] Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FRERUTHERFORD
Title: Rutherford
Description: Rocket Labâ€™s flagship engine, the 4,900lbf Rutherford, is an electrical turbo-pumped LOX/RP-1 engine specifically designed for the Electron Launch Vehicle. [0.3m] Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FREP80
Title: P80
Description: The P80 is an high-performance European Solid Rocket Motor. It powers the first stage of the Vega launch vehicle and may be upgraded to an heavier and more powerful version in order to boost Ariane 6. The P80 SRM is currently the largest and most powerfull single segment solid rocket motor. Burn time ~110s.[3m] Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FRELE5
Title: LE-5 Series
Description: Advanced upper stage hydrolox japanese engines developped by Mitsubishi. The LE-5 powers the H-II launch vehicle second stage. [1.5m] Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FRERUTHERFORDVAC
Title: Rutherford Vacuum
Description: The Rutherford engine with an extended nozzle for better vacuum performance. [0.6m] Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FRELE7
Title: LE-7 Series
Description: 1990s medium TWR, atmospheric and vacuum use. Fuel-rich staged combustion engines used on the core stage of H-II series launchers. The original LE-7 was replaced by the LE-7A, which sacrificed some performance in favor of reduced cost and better reliability. Diameter: [3.0 m]. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FREZEFIRO9
Title: Zefiro 9
Description: The Zephiro 9 is an high performance upper stage solid rocket motor. It powers Vega's third stage. Burn time ~120s. [1.9m] Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FRERD843
Title: RD-843
Description: The RD-843 is a Ukrainian single nozzle liquid propellant rocket engine powering Vega fourth stage (AVUM). Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FREVIKINGEARLY
Title: Viking (2/2B)
Description: Early Viking engines used on Ariane 1, 2 and 3. Thanks to the magic of hypergolic propellant, Vikings engines were able to achieve a substainable amount of thrust at all altitude. Includes configs for Viking 2 and 2B. [1.5m] Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FREVIKINGUPPER
Title: Viking (4/4B)
Description: Upper stage Viking engine used on Ariane 1 and 4 as well as on Indian Lauch Vehicles GSLV and PSLV. Includes configs for Viking 4, 4B, Vikas 2, 2B and X. [1.8m] Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FREVIKINGLOWER
Title: Viking (5B/5C/6)
Description: Later Viking engines used on Ariane 4. Includes configs for Viking 5B, 5C and 6 (liquid fuel booster). [1.5m] Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FREFRE2
Title: FRE-2
Description: The Firefly Research Engine 2 (FRE-2) is a lower stage aerospike-clustered engine developped by Firefly, and intended to be used with the Firefly Alpha launch vehicle. Using an aerospike noozle surrounded by twelve combustion chambers, the FRE-2 is efficient at a wide range of altitude. The Firefly engines will burn RP1 on the first flights, but they will be upgraded to burn Methane and therefore improve their efficiency. [1.85m] Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FREZEFIRO23
Title: Zefiro 23
Description: The Zephiro 23 is an high performance upper stage solid rocket motor. It powers Vega's second stage. Burn time ~77s. [1.9m] Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: HA3SLRD171
Title: RD-171
Description: The RD-170 and RD-171 engines consisted of 4 chambers, 1 turbo-pump and 2 gas generators were developed simultaneously, the difference being one-plane gimballing in the RD-170 used in the Energia launch vehicle strap-ons versus two-plane gimablling in the RD-171 used on the first stage of the Zenit launch vehicle. The RD-171 can be gimballed using bellows to 6 degrees normally but it has reached 8-10 degrees in tests. The chamber conditions are 300 atmosphere pressure and at a 400 degrees C oxygen-rich gas mixture - very dangerous conditions. The RD-170 was very hard to prove and many designers thought it couldn't be done. The first stage strap-ons were recovered under parachutes and returned to Baikonur for study. The engine was designed for 10 reuses but tests showed they could stand up to 20 burns.

Name: HA3SLRP2FuelTank2-1
Title: Zenit First Stage Tank
Description: First stage tank for Zenit.

Name: HA3SLSAS
Title: Zenit Instrument Unit
Description: The Zenit Instrument Unit provides command and control for the final stages of the Zenit series vehicles. Could be used with any other 3.90m launch vehicles.

Name: HA3SLRetroRocket
Title: Zenit Retro Rocket
Description: Skootches away those used stages.

Name: HA3SLPayloadFairingLong
Title: Zenit Fairing Extended
Description: When you have bigger loads, you need bigger covers!

Name: HA3SLStage1Decoupler
Title: Zenit stage 1 decoupler
Description: First stage decoupler for Zenit. Attach between the first and second stages.

Name: HA3SLStage2FuelTank
Title: Zenit Second Stage Tank
Description: Second stage tank for Zenit.

Name: HA3SLRD58M
Title: RD-58Z Block D
Description: Adaptation of Block D for Zenit.

Name: HorizonAeronautics_PF_Side
Title: FW - Conic Fairing
Description: Made from the finest materials found in the fields around the Space Center. Conic version.

Name: HA3SLCenterDecoupler
Title: Zenit stage 2 decoupler
Description: Second stage decoupler for Zenit. Attach between the second stage and Block D shroud.

Name: HA3SLRD120
Title: RD-120
Description: High altitude engine used in the Zenit second stage. First production Russian engine to be test fired in the United States (3 test burns were made).

Name: HA3SLPayloadDecoupler
Title: FB - Zenit Payload Adapter
Description: Payload adapter for Zenit. Includes nodes for Procedural Fairings

Name: HA3SLPayloadFairing
Title: Zenit Fairing
Description: Keeps the shaft slick and quick

Name: HA3SLStageShroud
Title: Zenit Block DM-SL Shroud
Description: Block DM-SL (a.k.a. Zenit 3rd stage) shroud. Attach it to Block DM-SL.

Name: K2Pod
Title: K2 Command Pod (2.5 m)
Description: A two-person pod. Features an offset Center of Mass to allow lifting reentry and an integrated bipropellant Attitude Control System (ACS) for controlled reentries. Heat shield rated for LEO reentries.

Name: KAS_Pylon1
Title: KAS/KIS - Pylon
Description: A simple part that can be used as a support for attaching stuff (ports, pipes, etc...)

Name: KAS_Strut1
Title: KAS/KIS - Strut
Description: End point for building a strut from EVA. Links are restricted to the same vessel. Useful for strengthening a vessel.

Name: KAS_CPort1
Title: KAS/KIS - Connector Port
Description: A multi-purpose port. Can be used to plug a winch connector or for building pipes. Useful for making ground bases and transferring resources.

Name: KAS_Winch2
Title: KAS/KIS - Winch (Radial)
Description: A winch used to extend and retract a cable. A hook or a connector port can be pre-attached if needed.

Name: KAS_Hook_GrapplingHook
Title: KAS/KIS - Grappling Hook
Description: This hook will attach to everything it collides with, as long as the impact is strong enough. Can be mounted on a winch. To be used with the winch eject function.

Name: KAS_Winch1
Title: KAS/KIS - Winch (Stack)
Description: A winch used to extend and retract a cable. A hook or a connector port can be pre-attached if needed.

Name: KAS_Hook_Harpoon
Title: KAS/KIS - Harpoon
Description: This hook will attach to everything it collides with, as long as the impact is strong enough. Can be mounted on a winch. To be used with the winch eject function.

Name: KAS_Hook_Magnet
Title: KAS/KIS - Electro-Magnet
Description: This electro-magnet is perfect for grabing heavy objects without a connector or a docking port. Can be mounted on a winch or on a hook support.

Name: KAS_Hook_Anchor
Title: KAS/KIS - Anchor
Description: An anchor to be used for boat, airship or everything else. In addition to its weight, it also provide drag and friction when touching the ground.

Name: ntr-sc-25-1
Description: Low thrust pump-fed expander nuclear engine. Evolved for the original NERVA design the Bimodal NTR, instead of wasting precious propellant mass for cooling the engine reactor, uses a Brayton cycle electricity generator unit to convert the waste thermal energy into useful electrical power. It also supports liquid oxygen injection (TRITON - trimodal operation) for increased thrust but with the cost of a lower overall efficiency. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: ntr-sc-125-1
Title: NERVA I
Description: 1970s low TWR vacuum engine. the NERVA (Nuclear Engine for Rocket Vehicle Applications) is designed for orbital tugs and large rocket upper stages. Diameter: [1.25 m]. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: ntr-sc-125-2
Title: NERVA II
Description: A later 70s atomic engine. Relatively low TWR but high ISP and power generation of 4200 MW. Derived from the Phoebus 2A ground demonstrator, tested in 1968. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: KK_Antares_RUAG937SPayloadAdapter
Title: Antares RUAG 937S Payload Adapter
Description: The RUAG 937S connects the Payload Adapter to the Castor 30 Payload Cone.

Name: KK_Antares_PayloadFairing
Title: Antares Payload Fairing
Description: The Antares Payload Fairing protects the payload during launch. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: KK_Antares_FirstStage
Title: Antares First Stage
Description: The first stage of Orbital Sciences Antares launch vehicle, powered by two AJ-26-62 engines, modified NK-33 engines. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: KK_Antares_PayloadFairing_e
Title: Antares Payload Fairing Extended
Description: The Antares Payload Fairing protects the payload during launch. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: KK_Antares_Interstage
Title: Antares Interstage
Description: Connects the payload fairing and first stage.

Name: KK_Antares_Castor30Cone
Title: Castor 30 Cone
Description: This is a segment attached between the Castor 30 and one of the payload attach fittings.

Name: KK_Antares_Castor30Adapter
Title: Antares Castor 30 Adapter
Description: Connects the Castor 30 to the Interstage.

Name: KK_SPX_F1S2FT
Title: Falcon 1 S2 Tank
Description: The second stage of SpaceX's Falcon 1 launch vehicle, equipped with a 3 axis attitude control system.

Name: KK_SPX_F1S1FT
Title: Falcon 1 S1 Fuel Tank (Merlin 1A version)
Description: The Falcon 1 first stage fuel tank is a simple design using a common bulkhead and a lightweight structure. It also is the most reliable part of Falcon 1+, not being a direct cause of any of its failures.

Name: KK_SPX_Kestrel
Title: Kestrel
Description: Second stage engine for the Falcon 1 rocket. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: KK_SPXF1_S2FT_ALT1e
Title: Falcon 1e S2 Tank
Description: The second stage of SpaceX's Falcon 1 launch vehicle, equipped with a 3 axis attitude control system.

Name: KK_SPXF1_S1FT_ALT1C
Title: Falcon 1 S1 Fuel Tank (Merlin 1C version)
Description: The Falcon 1 first stage fuel tank is a simple design using a common bulkhead and a lightweight structure. It also is the most reliable part of Falcon 1+, not being a direct cause of any of its failures.

Name: KK_SPX_Merlin1Ci
Title: Merlin 1A/1C
Description: Merlin 1Ci was the first successful engine designed by SpaceX. It was flown on the Falcon 1+, the first Falcon rocket to attain orbit. A moderately powerful engine with a gimbaled turbopump exhaust for roll control, it is well suited for launching small payloads into low orbits. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: KK_SPX_F1IS
Title: Falcon 1 Interstage
Description: An interstage connecting the Falcon 1 first and second stages. A simple composite design fitted with explosive bolts.

Name: KK_SPX_Falcon9_FC
Title: SpaceX Falcon 9 Flight Control System
Description: Flight Control unit for SpaceX Falcon 9. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: KK_SPX_F1Fairing
Title: Falcon 1 Fairing
Description: The Fairing protects the Falcon 1's payload during ascent. The fairing gets jettisonned after ignition of the Kestrel second stage's engine.

Name: KK_SPX_FalconGridfin
Title: SpaceX Gridfin
Description: These fins help SpaceX to steer their Falcon 9 first stage back to the ground using the atmosphere. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: KK_SPX_F9FT_Interstage_RCS
Title: Falcon 9 Full Thrust Interstage RCS Unit
Description: An improved version of the Falcon 9 1.1 Interstage RCS unit. Its thrusters are a little more powerful, the weight was slightly reduced, as was the drag. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: KK_SPX_F912_Interstage_RCS
Title: Falcon 9 Interstage RCS Unit
Description: A small Reaction Control System block, featuring 4 small thrusters combined into a single body. This RCS unit gets attached in a pair to the Falcon 9 1.1/1.1 FT interstage, to reorient the first stage of the Falcon 9 rocket after its seperation. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: KK_SPX_FalconGridfin_FT
Title: SpaceX Gridfin (Full Thrust)
Description: These fins help SpaceX to steer their Falcon 9 first stage back to the ground using the atmosphere. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: KK_KK_SPX_ITS_booster_gridfin
Title: ITS Booster Gridfin
Description: (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: KK_SPX_ITS_ship_flapR
Title: SpaceX ITS Ship Body Flap (Right)
Description: (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: KK_SPX_ITS_ship_flapL
Title: SpaceX ITS Ship Body Flap (Left)
Description: (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: KK_SPX_ITS_booster_RCS
Title: SpaceX ITS Booster RCS Thruster
Description: (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: RO_KWsrbGlobeI_GEM
Title: GEM 40
Description: The Graphite-Epoxy Motor (GEM) replaced the steel case used on earlier Castor-series boosters with a lighter composite case. The 40-inch (1-meter) diameter GEM 40 was used on the Delta II 7000-series in sets of three, four, or nine. When nine boosters were used, six were ignited at liftoff and the remaining three were ignited after burnout and jettison of the first six. Burn time: 58 seconds. Diameter: [1.02 m]. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: KW1mDecoupler
Title: KW Stack Decoupler [Small]
Description: KW Stack Decoupler. Low Profile. Small.

Name: KW5mengineTitanV
Title: J-2 Engine
Description: Cluster of five (5) Rocketdyne J-2 engines as found on the Saturn V.

Name: KWsrbGlobeVI
Title: AJ-60A
Description: The AJ-60A was developed for the Atlas V, which can be configured with up to five boosters. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: KW2mengineVestaVR9D
Title: 2 x LE-7A
Description: Dual LE-7A engines are used on the core stage of the H-2B launcher. These staged combustion engines burn hydrogen/LOX and are throttleable to 72% of maximum thrust. [5.0 m] Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: KW2mengineGriffonG8D
Title: RD-107/108 Series [2.0 m]
Description: The engine series built for the R-7, Vostok, Soyuz, and it's derivative Molynia launch vehicles.

Name: RO_KWsrbGlobeI
Title: Castor 4AXL
Description: Strap-on booster, improvement of Castor 4A, first tested May 1992. Its 30% performance increase would improve performance of Atlas IIAS, H-II, and other vehicles. First flight 2001. Diameter: [1.02 m]. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: KWFlatadapter3x1
Title: KW Flat Adapter [3:1]
Description: KW Flat Adapter. 3:1 ratio.

Name: KWFlatadapter3x2
Title: KW Flat Adapter [3:2]
Description: KW Flat Adapter. 3:2 ratio.

Name: RO_KWsrbGlobeI_Castor4
Title: Castor 4
Description: The Castor 4 was developed as the second stage of the Athena H missile and first flew in 1971. It was later adapted to replace Delta's Castor 2 boosters, increasing GTO capacity from 1593 lb (723 kg) to nearly 2000 lb (900 kg). The resulting Delta 3000-series launched in 1975 and was the first to adopt a staggered booster staging sequence. Previous Delta vehicles burned their motors in a 6-3 sequence and then jettisoned all SRMs at once. The heavier and longer-burning Castor 4 required that the ground-lit motors be jettisoned immediately after depletion to reduce dead weight. Early launches used a less efficient 5-4 sequence to reduce acceleration but returned to a 6-3 sequence after Delta was strengthened in the early 80s. Diameter: [1.02 m]. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: KWsrbUllage
Title: Saturn V S-II Retrorocket
Description: Four of these were installed on the S-IVB Aft Interstage and stayed attached to the S-II upon separation of that stage. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: KW3mFairingCone
Title: KW Fairing Cone Third [Large]
Description: KW Fairing Cone Third [Large]
